main event: A very large white light resembling a star was observed traveling at a medium course for 35 seconds before disappearing instantaneously.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 35 seconds,The object resembled a meteor,The sighting occurred on 5 February 1961,The object was reported to have a tail similar to a large meteor,There was no vertical motion observed in the object's trajectory.
sighted object: a large white light resembling a star
location: Cape Prince of Wales, Alaska, USA
